Error: `&` address-positioned marker requires an X- or Y-indexed addressing mode
   ╭─[ tests/golden/fixtures/syntax-addrmode-amp-stack-rel-err/input.k65:4:5 ]
   │
 4 │     lda &FIELD_HP, s
   │     ────────┬───────  
   │             ╰───────── address-positioned marker on non-indexed operand
   │ 
   │ Help: use `&EXPR, x` or `&EXPR, y` — without an index register the operand IS the address, so a value-as-offset reading makes no sense
   │ 
   │ Note: The `&EXPR` marker says "let this value play the role of the operand in `dp,X` / `abs,X` (or `,Y`) addressing." That's only meaningful when an index register adds the runtime base; in plain direct/absolute the operand is already the address.
───╯
